nefits associated with both liberalism and communitarianism. The book explores fundamental issues concerning freedom, rights, authority, public moral education, the relation between the public and the private, and the role of social criticism in democracies. Isolating the merits and liabilities of both liberal and communitarian theories, the author demonstrates that we need not be in the position of having to choose between them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aSociology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478081040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804780810423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804780810/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles